{
  "title": "ISic000063. Honours for the Emperor Trajan",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Imperator  Caesar  divi  Nervae \n                     filius  Nerva  Traianus  Augustus \n                    Germanicus  Dacicus\"><span data-text=\"Imperator\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">Imp(erator)</span> ❦ <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Caesar\"><span data-text=\"Caesar\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">Caesar</span></span> ❦ <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"divi  Nervae\"><span data-text=\"divi\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">divi</span> ❦ <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Nervae\"><span data-text=\"Nervae\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">Nervae</span></span></span> ❦ <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>❦ <span data-text=\"filius\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">f(ilius)</span> ❦ <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Nerva\"><span data-text=\"Nerva\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">Nerva</span></span> ❦ <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Traianus\"><span data-text=\"Traianus\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"\">Traianus</span></span> ❦ <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Augustus\"><span data-text=\"Augustus\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"\">Aug(ustus)</span></span> ❦ <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Germanicus\"><span data-text=\"Germanicus\" data-n=\"90\" data-lemma=\"\">Germanicus</span></span> ❦ <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Dacicus\"><span data-text=\"Dacicus\" data-n=\"100\" data-lemma=\"\">Dacicus</span></span></span> ❦ <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"pontifex\" data-n=\"110\" data-lemma=\"\">pontifex</span>  <span data-text=\"maximus\" data-n=\"115\" data-lemma=\"\">maximus</span> ❦ <br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"tribunicia\" data-n=\"125\" data-lemma=\"\">tr(ibunicia)</span> ❦ <span data-text=\"potestate\" data-n=\"135\" data-lemma=\"\">pot(estate)</span> ❦ <span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII</span> ❦ <span data-text=\"imperator\" data-n=\"150\" data-lemma=\"\">imp(erator)</span> ❦ <span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII</span> ❦ <br id=\"al6-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-text=\"consul\" data-n=\"165\" data-lemma=\"\">co(n)s(ul)</span> ❦ V ❦ <span data-text=\"pater\" data-n=\"180\" data-lemma=\"\">p(ater)</span> ❦ <span data-text=\"patriae\" data-n=\"190\" data-lemma=\"\">p(atriae)</span> ❦ </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/FZWWPUD6</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Imperator  Caesar  divi  Nervae \n                     filius  Nerva  Traianus  Augustus \n                    Germanicus  Dacicus\"><span data-text=\"Imperator\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">IMP</span>❦<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Caesar\"><span data-text=\"Caesar\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">CAESAR</span></span>❦<span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"divi  Nervae\"><span data-text=\"divi\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">DIVI</span>❦<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Nervae\"><span data-text=\"Nervae\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">NERVAE</span></span></span>❦<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>❦<span data-text=\"filius\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">F</span>❦<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Nerva\"><span data-text=\"Nerva\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">NERVA</span></span>❦<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Traianus\"><span data-text=\"Traianus\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"\">TRAIANUS</span></span>❦<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Augustus\"><span data-text=\"Augustus\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"\">AUG</span></span>❦<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Germanicus\"><span data-text=\"Germanicus\" data-n=\"90\" data-lemma=\"\">GERMANICUS</span></span>❦<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Dacicus\"><span data-text=\"Dacicus\" data-n=\"100\" data-lemma=\"\">DACICUS</span></span></span>❦<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"pontifex\" data-n=\"110\" data-lemma=\"\">PONTIFEX</span><span data-text=\"maximus\" data-n=\"115\" data-lemma=\"\">MAXIMUS</span>❦<br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"tribunicia\" data-n=\"125\" data-lemma=\"\">TR</span>❦<span data-text=\"potestate\" data-n=\"135\" data-lemma=\"\">POT</span>❦<span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII</span>❦<span data-text=\"imperator\" data-n=\"150\" data-lemma=\"\">IMP</span>❦<span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">IIII</span>❦<br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-text=\"consul\" data-n=\"165\" data-lemma=\"\">COS</span>❦V❦<span data-text=\"pater\" data-n=\"180\" data-lemma=\"\">P</span>❦<span data-text=\"patriae\" data-n=\"190\" data-lemma=\"\">P</span>❦</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic000063_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-05-23\" src=\"ISic000063_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000063.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-05-23\" src=\"ISic000063-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of IMusPalermo</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014\">Alfredo Tosques</a></p>  <p>Emperor Caesar, son of the deified Nerva, Nerva Trajan Augustus Germanicus Dacicus, Pontifex Maximus, holding tribunician power for the seventh time, acclaimed imperator for the fourth time, consul for the fifth time, father of the fatherland.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0009-2753-4014\">Alfredo Tosques</a></p>  <p>L’imperatore Cesare, figlio del divo Nerva, Nerva Traiano Augusto Germanico Dacico, pontefice massimo, investito della potestà tribunizia per la settima volta, imperatore per la quarta volta, console per la quinta volta, padre della patria.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Roman imperial dedications normally follow a very rigid structure, with the emperor and his full titulature in the dative case at the beginning, followed by the dedicants in the nominative at the end of the text. In this inscription, however, the Emperor appears unusually in the nominative, with no dedicants mentioned. This may indicate that the inscription commemorated an act of imperial euergetism (public benefaction) carried out by the Emperor himself. If this were the case, as the agent rather than the dedicatee, the use of the nominative would be explained.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Maggiore 1829 298 no.4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002795\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002795</a>  </li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650805\" target=\"_blank\">7472</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a></li><li> Bivona 1970 64 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142</a></li><li> Raepsaet-Charlier 1974 126 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001648\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001648</a></li><li> Manganaro 1988 73 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a></li><li> Fasolo 2013 71 no.2 fig.32 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1-6  68-75  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
